Current Champions League winners Liverpool, began the defence of their title on a bad note, losing 2-0 to Napoli. With the game looking to end goalless, the hosts were awarded a penalty with eight minutes left. Dries Mertens stepped up and gave his side the lead from the spot. In added time, Fernando Llorente pounced on a loose pass, to seal the win. Rodrigo scored the only goal, as Valencia beat Chelsea 1-0 at Stamford Bridge. The game between Borussia Dortmund and Barcelona ended 0-0, with Marcos Reus missing a penalty in the second half. Ajax thrashed Lille 3-0, Inter Milan drew 1-1 with Slavia Prague and RB Leipzig won 2-1 at Benfica. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.